        {
          "username": "Larry Depp",
          "rating": 3,
          "contributor_id": "118437779445955058140",
          "user_review_count": 8,
          "user_photo_count": 9,
          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVBvCRKju_ZWQ-9qD3f6BDLzGza263LLTPZTlYxgY2l8_sXmRm4CQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba12-br100",
          "description": "This clinic has helped me stay off heroin for over 4 years! Helped me get my life together! But I do have to say the staff is horrendous! It's nothing but a job and money for them! Your recovery doesn't mean a thing. Only good people that work in the building is security!!",
          "link": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sChZDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSUR5eS03eWRREAE!2m1!1s0x0:0xc8c354813f7ea5b1!3m1!1s2@1:CIHM0ogKEICAgIDyy-7ydQ%7C%7C?hl=en",
          "date": "5 years ago",
          "date_iso8601": "2021-03-17T15:30:15+00:00"
        },
        {
          "username": "Dariush Shojai",
          "rating": 5,
          "contributor_id": "114967511544100090478",
          "user_review_count": 20,
          "user_photo_count": 0,
          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI0mrWr8OlsbCbds55Pw8mgXE2lxgN76l_y4yPnSkRoyoatSA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba12-br100",
          "description": "I have been a client for only about a month or so, and I have to say that this clinic isbrun professionally, efficiently, and also extremely importantly: with kindness and understanding. I'm in the process for signing up for 2 weekly outpatient groups to further help me in my path to recovery and keep me focused.  Obviously, there will always be drama and conflict and everything else that comes with serious drug addiction-lets not forget, this is a methadone program.  Its unspokenly expected that there'll be issues,hence security guards and a no loitering zone like most other methadone programs also instill.  If you're in here to save your life from the abusive and painful cycle of drug addiction, I've yet to see a clinic with the vast medical and social services on site.  I highly recommend this program to anyone struggling with opiate addiction and is finally ready to quit.  Also, its location is right around the block from Penn Station, so its an extremely quick and convenient commute.",
          "link": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sChdDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSUQwNDl5WDRnRRAB!2m1!1s0x0:0xc8c354813f7ea5b1!3m1!1s2@1:CIHM0ogKEICAgID049yX4gE%7C%7C?hl=en",
          "date": "6 years ago",
          "date_iso8601": "2019-11-18T15:22:54+00:00"
        },
        {
          "username": "daniel dziedzic",
          "rating": 3,
          "contributor_id": "111788115491028505903",
          "user_review_count": 14,
          "user_photo_count": 0,
          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKEak3Rt_rGoyahGWIi0H3pxZGU6TksNnhayyTxhWmp13tOyA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100",
          "description": "When signing up process was easy. Just come in between 7am-10am. Only thing is you have to give urine sample and then WAIT a few days for them to call you back. So if you are struggling its unfortunate they make you wait days before getting medicated. Other than that from what I've seen and heard, typical clinic.",
          "link": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sChdDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSUNhdXU3Vm1nRRAB!2m1!1s0x0:0xc8c354813f7ea5b1!3m1!1s2@1:CIHM0ogKEICAgICauu7VmgE%7C%7C?hl=en",
          "date": "4 years ago",
          "date_iso8601": "2021-07-29T12:07:49+00:00"
        },
        {
          "username": "Leo Kaplus",
          "rating": 1,
          "contributor_id": "115307721116209641144",
          "user_review_count": 7,
          "user_photo_count": 0,
          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXHJLkYnO4kE4y0ue2PJtcpywGM9yF8EdhOBaDhAck3uHRdi9g=s120-c-rp-mo-br100",
          "description": "Well..You must be a street addict to receive help here. The thousands of us who have been under a doctors care for medical reasons. Who are being forced off that medical care due to Pressure from the government to stop prescribing opiates. Have been taking opiates with a good quality of life for over 35 years.  I would say I am quite addicted to opiates but I don't deserve help from this so called caring facility.  Hence forth I will Lie cheat, do whatever I must to survice\u2026 Being truthful..I guess is a sign of weakness.....Maybe Trump has something after all...I never though so before\n***Lady I spoke with did seem caring and sympathetic but was not in a position to do anything.",
          "link": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sChdDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSUNvdVl5N25BRRAB!2m1!1s0x0:0xc8c354813f7ea5b1!3m1!1s2@1:CIHM0ogKEICAgICouYy7nAE%7C%7C?hl=en",
          "date": "7 years ago",
          "date_iso8601": "2018-10-25T19:52:40+00:00"
        },
        {
          "username": "Janice Jacome",
          "rating": 4,
          "contributor_id": "113453814608904045090",
          "user_review_count": 25,
          "user_photo_count": 1,
          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX4Zhpxv6hlL02hZ_0cmtCeMoRXVGqpwMisjiWbTGBc_y5dt1Iq2w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba12-br100",
          "description": "Used to be the LAST RESORT for all methadone drop outs...Now staff is polite, professional,and caring without being OVERBEARING. I am happy l switched BUT do need to modernize type of meth given, ( still using orange diskettes/ white) when majority NY uses cherry liquid dispensed by computer",
          "link": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sChZDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSURNcUt6R05BEAE!2m1!1s0x0:0xc8c354813f7ea5b1!3m1!1s2@1:CIHM0ogKEICAgIDMqKzGNA%7C%7C?hl=en",
          "date": "6 years ago",
          "date_iso8601": "2019-12-15T01:14:12+00:00"
        },
        {
          "username": "Curtis Samuel \u201cSam\u201d Safran",
          "rating": 4,
          "contributor_id": "106201534991424054033",
          "user_review_count": 48,
          "user_photo_count": 499,
          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWNVITDqAUyrJI8ZmsNxnxf5Y_8pogPWIlHH5iAN9aZbvS42Y63gw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba12-br100",
          "description": "Though it's probably not as professional as a Hospital's Maintenance Clinic, (and certainly not as clean, not as up-to-date, & an older building, it's about what you'd expect for a Methadone Clinic.  Most of the Staff is pretty nice, too. (Oh, & if you don't want to do Methadone Maintenance, they offer Suboxone, too!)\n\nPlus, the TWO MAJOR Positives about it, over other Clinics, are: 1: it has the Methadone Wafers (you can choose between the White or the Orange ones,) as opposed to the Syrup!  & 2: It has the some of (if not THE MOST) Convenient Hours - open Weekdays from 7, or 7:30am-5:30pm, and Saturdays it's open from 7, or 7:30am-12pm!   (The only thing is, on Weekdays, they're closed for an hour, between 2:30p-3:30p, but that's no big deal, IMHO, seeing as they're open until 5:30p!)\n\nI wouldn't recommend using their Psychiatrist, though - IF they even still have one!!!\n\nAll in all, I wouldn't switch Clinics for the life of Me! (& I'm SUPER Happy with my Counselor, Dorian - would TOTALLY Recommend him to Everyone!!!)",
          "link": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sChdDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSUNnMzdtaGhRRRAB!2m1!1s0x0:0xc8c354813f7ea5b1!3m1!1s2@1:CIHM0ogKEICAgICg37mhhQE%7C%7C?hl=en",
